The paper deals with a geometric problem involving sets of points in the plane, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The problem involves finding a minimum spanning graph that satisfies certain connectivity constraints, which suggests that it also belongs to the graph theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The use of matroid techniques to solve the problem suggests that it may also belong to the combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) sub-category. The problem is motivated by ink minimization for set visualizations, which suggests that it may also belong to the information visualization (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with algorithmic problems and their complexity, which suggests that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
